üöÄ The 4-Step Implementation Path
1. Institutional Alignment (Weeks 1-2)
‚Ä¢	Goal: Identify a Faculty Lead and secure "Capstone" or "Lab" credit status for participants.
‚Ä¢	Key Asset: Partnership Proposal Template.
2. Recruitment & Training (Weeks 3-8)
‚Ä¢	Goal: Form multidisciplinary teams (Code, Business, Design).
‚Ä¢	Activity: Deploy the weekly masterclasses found in the /Presenters folder.
‚Ä¢	The "No-Edit" Rule: Introduce the core constraint: Business plans must be generated and refined via prompts, not manual typing.
3. Local Campus Qualifier (Week 12)
‚Ä¢	Goal: Crown a local champion to represent your college in the State Finals.
‚Ä¢	Activity: Use the Judging Rubric to ensure parity with the statewide league standards.
4. The Maryland AI Cup (Week 15)
‚Ä¢	Goal: The top 2 teams from your campus advance to the Annapolis-based finale to pitch to VCs and state leaders.
________________________________________
‚öñÔ∏è Governance & Rules
To maintain the integrity of the league, all facilitators must enforce the Startathon AI "Prompt-Only" Protocol:
1.	Teams must test at least 5 different LLMs (e.g., GPT-4, Claude 3.5, Gemini Pro).
2.	All business plan refinements must be documented in a Prompt Sequence Log.
3.	Direct manual editing of the AI output is prohibited (emphasizing the skill of AI Orchestration).
